gobblin.data.management.copy.converter

Class DecryptConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.converter.Converter<String,String,FileAwareInputStream,FileAwareInputStream>
      • gobblin.data.management.copy.converter.DistcpConverter
        • gobblin.data.management.copy.converter.DecryptConverter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FinalState, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class DecryptConverter
extends DistcpConverter
    Converter that decrypts an InputStream. The encryption algorithm will be selected by looking at the converter.encrypt.algorithm configuration key in the job. See EncryptionConfigParser for more details. If no algorithm is specified then the converter will default to gpg for backwards compatibility reasons.

      • extensionsToRemove

        public List<String> extensionsToRemove()
        Overrides:
        extensionsToRemove in class DistcpConverter
        Returns:
        A list of extensions that should be removed from the output file name, which will be applied in order. For example, if this method returns ["gz", "tar", "tgz"] then "file.tar.gz" becomes "file".
